1. Installing the vnc server; type
  
  sudo apt-get install tightvncserver
  
2. Check vnc server is running or not; type
  
   vncserver :1

3. To ensure vnc server running automatically after boot up,
  
  a. type
  
     sudo nano /etc/rc.local

  b. Between fi and exit 0; type

    su - pi -c'/usr/bin/vncserver :'
   
   then press cntrl+X (exit and save) 
   
